@doctorsuevarma shares her five priorities in helping individuals and communities heal from collective trauma. The role of self-compassion is key- to promote mental health treatment as well as tangible next steps. 
Promoting a sense of safety, calm, connection, hope, and self-efficacy are evidence based priorities after trauma as well as community based-interventions. Dr. Sue Varma is a Board certified psychiatrist, Cognitive behavioral therapist, couples and family therapist, Clinical Assistant Professor at NYU Langone, former 9/11 medical director at the World Trade Center Mental Health program at NYU, and Distinguished Fellow of the American Psychiatric Association, discussing. She is a frequent media contributor to all the major news outlets. She talks about the #4msofmentalhealth and provides tangible tips on her IG @doctorsuevarma. One in four people live with a mental health condition (and these figures are now on the rise amidst the pandemic). Please share this with anyone who could benefit from a mindset boost. We need to focus on prevention just as much as treatment. #self compassion #trauma #collectivetrauma

#optimism #stigmafree #mentalhealthawarenessmonth
